Title: A Survey Of Oscillations And Granulation In Subgiant Stars

PI: Huber, Daniel - University Of Hawaii (Manoa)

Type: SMALL

Summary: Brightness variations observed in high-precision light curves encode powerful information about fundamental properties and convection in subgiant stars through oscillations and granulation. However, the current sample of subgiants with measured oscillations and granulation is predominantly focused on the Kepler field, and prime mission TESS data do not provide sufficient time coverage to make precise measurements. Here we propose 2-minute cadence observations to perform a survey of oscillations and granulation in subgiant stars, which will enable us to (i) probe the efficiency of convective driving and damping of oscillations, (ii) test stellar models by constraining convective properties such as the mixing length parameter and (iii) calibrate granulation metrics for TESS stars.
